Pressure is mounting on the KwaZulu-Natal health department to fast-track the opening of the newly built Dr Pixley Ka Isaka Seme Memorial Hospital in Durban. eNCA's Thuba Vilane has the details. #DStv403​ #eNCA DURBAN - Pressure is mounting on the KwaZulu-Natal health department to fast-track the opening of the newly built Dr Pixley Ka Isaka Seme Memorial Hospital in Durban. Construction of the R2.8-billion facility began in 2015 and should have been completed in 2018. Unions are now demanding that the hospital be opened. READ: KZN has enough beds in public hospitals: Health HoD The National Education Health and Allied Workers' Union says this would help ease congestion at nearby facilities. Citing that Mahatma Gandhi hospital and other health facilities are already overcrowded. Nehawu says the hospital must be up and running by March.